    pearls: ["The 5Ms of Geriatrics (Mind, Mobility, Medications, Multi-complexity, Matters Most) provide a comprehensive framework that ensures no critical geriatric domain is overlooked during assessment","CGA has been shown to reduce mortality, decrease institutionalization, and improve functional status and cognitive outcomes compared to usual care in hospitalized and community-dwelling older adults","Frailty is distinct from disability and comorbidity -- a frail patient may have no identified diseases but exhibits vulnerability to stressors with poor physiologic reserve","The Timed Up and Go (TUG) test is a validated, efficient fall risk screen: patient rises from chair, walks 3 meters, turns, walks back, and sits -- > 12 seconds suggests increased fall risk","Always ask about the 'geriatric giants': falls, confusion (delirium/dementia), incontinence, immobility, and iatrogenic harm -- these are sentinel events in older adults","Advance care planning is a process, not a single event -- revisit goals of care at every significant health change, hospitalization, or transition of care"],
