    pearls: ["Late-onset depression presents differently from earlier-onset: apathy, psychomotor retardation, and executive dysfunction predominate over sadness and guilt -- clinicians must ask beyond 'Do you feel sad?'","The GDS-15 was specifically designed for older adults and excludes somatic items (sleep, appetite, fatigue) that overlap with normal aging and medical illness, making it more specific than PHQ-9 in this population","Depressive pseudodementia is distinguished from Alzheimer disease by: rapid onset, 'I don't know' answers, prominent depressive symptoms preceding cognitive decline, and improvement with antidepressant treatment","SIADH-induced hyponatremia is a significant SSRI risk in older adults, especially those on thiazide diuretics or with low BMI -- check sodium at baseline and within 2 weeks of SSRI initiation","Older white males have the highest suicide completion rate of any demographic group; they use more lethal means and are less likely to communicate intent -- always perform structured suicide risk assessment","Vascular depression associated with white matter disease responds less well to antidepressants and has higher recurrence rates -- aggressive cardiovascular risk factor management is essential as adjunctive treatment"],
